The paper focuses on evaluating visual representations, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of self-supervised learning techniques, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of linear probes, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset for temporal activity localization, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
